{
  "name": "RPlog_Imperial_Negotiations",
  "title": "Imperial Negotiations",
  "summary": "Deep within the mutant-haunted Abyssal Ruins beneath Coruscant, the Corellian operative Tyler Damion guides Captain Jarek Syris and Sergeant Tanis to a fortified safe house, where they are joined by the crimson Twi'lek crimelord Tyy'sun Eson, his slave Lavender, and his bodyguards Sidi Ren and Siva. Over cups of caf, Tyler lays out an audacious plan to topple the New Republic's military base by planting charges at its undercity foundation while striking the surface simultaneously, plunging Coruscant into the chaos that would ease an Imperial return. Eson questions whether anarchy truly serves him, but Jarek argues persuasively that the coming shift in power is inevitable and that an alliance with the future Imperial occupiers is the wiser bet. Eson agrees to provide reconnaissance and slicers in exchange for the group first assaulting and seizing a rival bunker for his Syndicate, a job that will harden their soldiers for the larger operation. With Jarek installed as overseer and Tanis volunteering to lead the recon, terms and payment are settled, sealing a lucrative underworld alliance before Tyler retires and the meeting concludes.",
